  "body": "Issues such as #4036 shows that headFetcher.HeadState() is not a safe function. It should:\r\n\r\n- Check if the state is nil, if so\r\n- Fallback into checking from the DB\r\n- If that fails or is nil, return an error\r\n\r\nThis will prevent most problems we have been seeing regarding panics at runtime",
